{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"background_color","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/background_color","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"\n<ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/background_color\">background_color</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/categories\">categories</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/description\">description</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/display\">display</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/display_override\">display_override</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/icons\">icons</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/name\">name</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/orientation\">orientation</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/prefer_related_applications\">prefer_related_applications</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/protocol_handlers\">protocol_handlers</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/related_applications\">related_applications</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/scope\">scope</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/screenshots\">screenshots</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/share_target\">share_target</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/short_name\">short_name</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/shortcuts\">shortcuts</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/start_url\">start_url</a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/theme_color\">theme_color</a></li></ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard experimental\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Experimental:</strong> <strong>This is an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Writing_guidelines/Experimental_deprecated_obsolete#experimental\">experimental technology</a></strong><br>Check the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">Browser compatibility table</a> carefully before using this in production.</p></div>\n<table class=\"properties\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">Type</th>\n      <td><code>String</code></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">Mandatory</th>\n      <td>No</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The <code>background_color</code> member defines a placeholder background color for the application page to display before its stylesheet is loaded. This value is used by the user agent to draw the background color of a shortcut when the manifest is available before the stylesheet has loaded.</p>\n<p>Therefore <code>background_color</code> should match the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-color\"><code>background-color</code></a> CSS property in the site's stylesheet for a smooth transition between launching the web application and loading the site's content.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> The <code>background_color</code> member is only meant to improve the user experience while the main stylesheet is loading from the network or the storage media; it is not used by the user agent as the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-color\"><code>background-color</code></a> CSS property when the progressive web app stylesheet is available.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: json notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token property\">\"background_color\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"red\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/manifest/#background_color-member","title":"Web Application Manifest"}],"query":"html.manifest.background_color"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"html.manifest.background_color","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/background_color/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The background_color member defines a placeholder background color for the application page to display before its stylesheet is loaded. This value is used by the user agent to draw the background color of a shortcut when the manifest is available before the stylesheet has loaded.","popularity":0.0009,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:38:45.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"background_color","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"background_color","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"background_color","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/manifest/background_color","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/manifest/background_color/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/f22e42182591e38590c9add80de91a51bce3cde2","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest","title":"Web app manifests"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/background_color","title":"background_color"}],"pageTitle":"background_color - Web app manifests | MDN","noIndexing":false}}